channel.title: 2 Guys 1 Cup AFL Podcast
channel.description: Wil Anderson and Charlie Clausen look at the week in footy (sort of).

item.title: 2G1C Presents The Footy Fixers: Captaincy
item.description: Has the process for selecting your clubs captain grown stale? The Footy Fixers say yes! So strap yourself in for some more revolutionary ideas that unsurprisingly involve a reality TV angle and/or fatalities.

item.title: 2G1C Presents The Footy Fixers: Father/Son
item.description: One of the most beloved quirks of our great game is the Father/Son rule, but could it be better? The Footy Fixers have the answers!

item.title: 2G1C Presents The Footy Fixers: Injuries
item.description: The Footy Fixers have been horrified by all the injuries this preseason and want find a solution that also provides extra entertainment for the fans.

item.title: 2G1C Presents The Footy Fixers: Fox Footy
item.description: The Footy Fixers turn their attention to the only dedicated footy channel around and ask if it's gotten to big for its own good.

item.title: 2G1C Presents The Footy Fixers: Preseason
item.description: As the new season approaches, the Footy Fixers look at the preseason and wonder if it could go for longer.

item.title: 2G1C Presents The Footy Fixers: Mascots
item.description: Do you think club mascots are getting stale, or worse, don't accurately reflect your club's identity? The Footy Fixers are here to shake things up with their all new line up of AFL mascots.

item.title: 2G1C Presents The Footy Fixers: Food Prices
item.description: What more expensive? Food at the footy or a wicker hanging egg chair from Aldi? The answer may surprise you, or most likely, not interest you at all.

item.title: 2G1C Presents The Footy Fixers: The Brownlow
item.description: Is footy's night of night's getting a little stale? What about an award for the league's worst player, or a live re-enactment of Mark Of The Year? The Footy Fixers have the answers.

item.title: 2G1C Presents The Footy Fixers: Cheer Squads
item.description: The Footy Fixers lament the demise of the banner run through and wonder if a strongman contest would be a good substitute.

item.title: 2G1C Presents The Footy Fixers: Deliberate Out-Of-Bounds
item.description: The Footy Fixers turn their attention to one of the most contentious rules in footy and suggest a way that tech could be its saviour.

item.title: 2G1C Presents The Footy Fixers: Moving The Grand Final From The MCG
item.description: The MCG has been the traditional home of the Grand Final, but is it the best home? As always the Footy Fixers have the answers.

item.title: 2G1C Presents The Footy Fixers: Trade Radio
item.description: What is the point of Trade Radio and should the entire thing be an It's A Knockout-style event? Charlie and Dools investigate.

item.title: 2G1C Presents The Footy Fixers: The Big Dance
item.description: In episode one of our summer series, Charlie and Scott Dooley debate the pros and cons of referring to the Grand Final as The Big Dance.

item.title: 2021 - 2 Guys 1 Cup & Junktime AFL Post Grand Final Spectacular
item.description: Our annual wrap up of the Grand Final with Michael Chamberlin and Adam Rozenbachs, featuring special guests Chas Licciardello, Broden Kelly and Titus O'Reilly.

item.title: 2021 - Gawn For A Dart, Gerard Wait-&-See vs Give 'Em A Kaning Pt 2, Naughty By Nature
item.description: In the last regular episode of 2021, Wil and Charlie talk about the Dees going the early crow, round up their reviews of the teams that made the eight and find out which Bulldog is a really good dancer. Get tickets to our post Grand Final Show with the boys from Junktime here:https://www.trybooking.com/events/landing?eid=803383&

item.title: 2021 - Smoking Banana Skins, Gerard Wait-&-See vs Give 'Em A Kaning, Mullet Over
item.description: Wil and Charlie sort through the aftermath of one of the most one-sided prelim weekends ever, the teams that didn't make the Final 8 are rated, listeners are still fascinated by haircuts. Get tickets to our post Grand Final Show with the boys from Junktime here:https://www.trybooking.com/events/landing?eid=803383&

item.title: 2021 - Proud Bottom Boy, Rhys' Revenge, West Australian Wig
item.description: Wil showed remarkable composure during the Bulldog's thrilling victory thanks to an edible, Nick Riewoldt can't help himself when in comes to the Cat's ruckman and a listener comes up with a fantastic rule for any team playing in WA. Get tickets to our post Grand Final show with the boys from Junktime here: https://www.trybooking.com/events/landing?eid=803383&

item.title: 2021 - Cody "The Tick" Weightman, What's Charlie Tweetin', In The Mouth Of Madness
item.description: In a surprising turn of events, Wil and Charlie find themselves talking about football. Is Charlie Cameron on a Twitter hiatus? Toby Greene's Pocket Profile is exhausting.

item.title: 2021 - Bevo's Bottom Boys, Playing The Stonk Market, Vibing With Piece
item.description: Wil is not feeling great about the Bulldogs' chances, but maybe it's all part of Bevo's plan. A crypto expert gives his take on Aker's Zucoin. JJ's pocket profile does not disappoint.

item.title: 2021 - 2 Coodabeens 1 Cup, Vale Class Of 2021, Inside The Blick Caves
item.description: Wil and Charlie realise their shtick is a lot like a legendary radio team. We say farewell to all the retiring players, even the ones we don't know. Wil is on fire during the Pocket Profile.

item.title: 2021 - The Underdog Dogs, How You'd Describe A Kid, Jason Hackeramanis
item.description: A weekend of carnage means the season can't end soon enough. Wil and Charlie get to know the Brisbane Lions a little too well. The last person you'd invest your money with has an offer that's too good to refuse.

item.title: 2021 - King Of The Candy Mansion, Choke On Deez Nuts, The Inscrutable Ben Brown
item.description: Wil and Charlie come up with a bold plan to keep Ben King at the Suns, Clarko's revenge on Hawthorn will be oh so sweet, Charlie derails Wil's Pocket Profile guesses with his worst clue yet.

item.title: 2021 - Twerping Coverage, Charles In Charge (Of Social Media), Biggs Play Big
item.description: Worlds collide when Kane Cornes chimes in on Rowelly's form, Charlie Cameron tweets up storm and the big Texan baffles Wil.

item.title: 2021 - Moving In To Marvel, The Best Nicknames, Layered Like A Cake
item.description: The season's on a knife's edge, will the AFL use their back up plan? Getting to know TEAC and Spare Keys. The Pocket Profile we've all been waiting for.

item.title: 2021 - Bring Out The Bully Tactics, Dunstan Checks In, #FreeDarcy
item.description: Each team should be allowed one old school bully tactic. How should the Saints handle Luke Dunstan's contract negotiations? Darcy Moore may nne

item.title: 2021 - Get Clarko On The Show, Getting To Know Hamburglar, Black Widow 7/10
item.description: Wil and Charlie wonder if they should devise a succession plan. The most requested Pocket Profile ever. Charles Cameron is a straight ahead kinda guy. Website: www.tofop.comSupport us on Patreon: www.patreon.com/tofopSee TOFOP Live: www.thegreataustralianpodcastfestival.com

item.title: 2021 - Don't Want No Hubs, Brodie's New Look, Here's To You, Sergio
item.description: All the teams are coming to Melbourne which sucks for Joe Daniher. Rowelly's taste in music is no surprise. Chris Fagan's Pocket Profile is heartwarming.

item.title: 2021 - Rohan's Revenge, The Anti PC GC, Being Brett Headyvich
item.description: Wil feels okay about losing to the Cats, Tony Cochrane goes nuts in an interview and Wil's inside the mind of an old school Eagle.

item.title: 2021 - Matt-matics, St Kill-Yourself, Clarko's A Genius
item.description: A quick rundown of the weekend's results reveals Wil knows nothing about tipping. What's going on with Matt Rowell's horticulture and what does Nick Bryan want to be when he grows up?

item.title: 2021 - Robbo's In The Woods, Gawn's Solid Set, Tigers Got That Strut
item.description: Buck's press conference is almost derailed by Robbo, Max Gawn lands every gag and thoughts on Adam Goodes.

item.title: 2021 - Forced Out Of Retirement, Forgot About Trey, Bucks Back To QLD
item.description: A twist is added to the mid-season draft, we learn more about everyone's favourite teaser pony, plus letters galore.

item.title: 2021 - Charlie's On The Edge, Bont's Vaccine Rollout, Grundy's Alternative Lite
item.description: After a horror performance by the Saints, Charlie's ready to pack it in. We finally find out Where Matt's At and Brody Grundy delivers an inscrutable pocket profile.

item.title: 2021 - The Son/Father Rule, Good Team Haircuts, The Buddy Prototype
item.description: Wil is fascinated by a weird little goal umpire, Charlie thinks he's in hell and the Pocket Profile is Ol' Circle Head.

item.title: 2021 - Borethorn, Hard Rubbish Ruckman, Prison Bar Tattoos
item.description: After the original (and more litigious) version of this episode was lost, Wil and Charlie reconvene to discuss Hawthorn's woes, the potential return of 211 and Port's FU to Collingwood.

item.title: 2021 - The Best Looking Ruckman, Western Australian Hair, Barks' 100
item.description: Does talent take longer to spread around a ruckman's body? David Mundy Needs A Makeover. Saints' legends hate reading.

item.title: 2021 - Derby/Darby, Freckles Are Funny, Imposter Le Cras
item.description: Medical sub Alex Williams comes off the bench to talk GWS and the Demons rise and tries to get inside the head of a Gold Coast Sun.

item.title: 2021 - Regarding Jordy, When Stevo Met Leo, Rowell For The Brownlow
item.description: Wil and Charlie think there might be a reason Jordan De Goey is getting concussed. The most up-to-date Pocket Profile yet. Bont likes it rough.

item.title: 2021 - Twerp Alert, Frampton's Terrible Rig, New Blues Song
item.description: Wil and Charlie bask in the glow of a winning weekend, find a website that feel the same way they do about Kane Cornes and come up with a new club song.

item.title: 2021 - A Bunch of Rhys Stanleys, Luko Needs A Personality, The Little QAnoner
item.description: Wil and Charlie wrap up Round 3 of the 2021 season and find out all about Jack Lukosius by analysing his Pocket Profile, which proves to be somewhat boring, plus, an old friend of the show joins guys on the line to catch up.. Follow 2G1C on Instagram: @2Guys1CupAFL

item.title: 2G1C Presents My Club: Talking Suns with Josh McConville
item.description: In the final episode of My Club, Charlie talks to Suns fan Josh McConville

item.title: 2021 - Chris Scott Gets Punchy, Walla Warms The Heart, Where's Matt At?
item.description: Wil and Charlie try and get to the bottom of the Cattery dust up, learn a bit more about Anthony McDonald-Tipungwuti and check in with that kid from the Gold Coast.

item.title: 2G1C Presents My Club: Talking Crows with Sam Mac
item.description: Sunrise weatherman and Gold Logie nominee Sam Mac joins Charlie to talk about his beloved Crows. Pre-order his book Accidental Weatherman: www.hachette.com.au/sam-mac/accidental-weatherman

item.title: 2021 - Your Daily Bailey, Sympathy For Rhys, We're Gonna Need More Footys
item.description: Wil & Charlie are back to chat all things from Round 1 - including the year's first pocket profile on Bailey Smith.

item.title: 2 Guys 1 Cup & Junktime AFL Grand Final Show 2020
item.description: Wil & Charlie team up with the Junktime AFL Podcast to chat the AFL Grand Final, and are joined by special guests Waleed Aly and Dave Thornton!

item.title: Joel Selwood's Charlie Brown Head, Jake Lloyd & Jimmy No Name, Marty Sex Worker
item.description: The end of the tumultuous 2020 AFL season is so close! Wil & Charlie makes their predictions for the Grand Final, chat Joel Selwood's Charlie Brown head, and a pocket profile from Marty Sex Worker.

item.title: The Tigers Turn Heel, Four Great Storylines, The Yankees Suck
item.description: We're nearing the end of the season, so who is looking likely to win the flag? + More CUNFE fiction, and an American listener writes in about baseball.

item.title: Gia Got A Fright, I Love My Dad/Coach, Grow Up Kayne Turner
item.description: Why has Gia's hair gone so grey so quickly? Which coach would you most want to be your dad? And Kayne Turner's Pocket Profile creates some anger in an all new 2G1C.

item.title: 2020 - Matt Murnane, Don't Wear It Out, Daniel Cross: We Hardly Knew You, Jack "Spoon" Redden
item.description: We're heading into finals season, and Wil & Charlie are back for Australia's favourite AFL adjacent podcast!https://www.trybooking.com/events/landing?eid=664923&

item.title: 2020 - Gerard Goes Full Hannibal, New Club, New Hair Cut, Wil's Best Mate
item.description: Wil & Charle are back for another week of Australia's favourite AFL-adjacent podcast, just before finals time! There's some more CUNFE fiction, plus the All-Australian team for 2020 has been announced!

item.title: 2020 - The Bombers Have Mental Scars, The Best Stories Of The Top 8, Pavatar: A Cunfe Sci-Fi Epic
item.description: Wil & Charlie are backing chatting about the best stories of the Top 8, as well as an amazing spoof of James Cameron's 'Avatar,' the latest listener submission to our Cunfe Fan Fiction.

item.title: 2020 - Playing Barefoot, The Banana Barney, Dude Where's My Kebab?
item.description: The biggest scandal of the week in AFL was the Richmond Tigers kebab and strippers controversy! Plus, playing AFL barefoot, more CUNFE fiction and a retro pocket profile!

item.title: The Real Hubwives Of Footy, Nat & Ben's Excellent Adventure, Jezza Loves Dogs
item.description: Another week of Australia's favourite AFL adjacent podcast sees Wil & Charlie round up on the week that was in AFL and even more CUNFE fiction!

item.title: 2020 - The Bulldogs Have A Trademark, Building On Sir Doug Nicholls Round, Shane Edwards: Enigma
item.description: Another round of footy is among us, and Wil & Charlie are talking everything that's happened in this week's episode of Australia's favourite AFL-adjacent podcast!

item.title: 2020 - Newnes Steals Every Schoolboy's Dream, No Coach Gets Sacked In 2020, Freaky Cunfe Day
item.description: Wil & Charlie think that no coach can be sacked after 2020, as it's been such a crazy day. We take a read of another listener submitted Cunfe fan fiction, and of course, the tips for the round ahead, as the Festival of Footy finally comes to an end.

item.title: 2020 - Is There Too Much Football Now?, Gerard Is Secretly Planning To Eat Robbo, Game Of Cunfe
item.description: Wil is in Stage 5 isolation... from football, and the guys are seriously asking the question, "Is there too much football now?" The boys chat all things AFL 360, including a theory that Gerard Whateley may be planning to eat Robbo, as well as some brand new entries to the universe of Cunfe fiction!

item.title: 2020 - Haircuts Are Good, Demons Are Bad, Daniel Concierge
item.description: This week on 2 Guys 1 Cup, all your usual AFL (and non-AFL) related content, including a Pocket Profile Pocket, some amazing new CUNFE fan-fiction and Daniel Concierge (?).

item.title: 2020 - Russell Rubbleson, Braydon Preuss' Concussion Test & Who Is Matthew Nicks?
item.description: This week, an AFL match actually takes place in the middle of the recording, with the AFL extravaganza taking place. However, as usual, Wil & Charlie are more interested in Cunfe Fiction, Russell Rubbleson (Robertson?), and debating whether or not Braydon Preuss' concussion is serious after reading his Pocket Profile.

item.title: 2020 - Round 8: Fyfington/Cunfe, Robbie Gray & Where's the Shinboner Spirit?
item.description: Would a streaming service pick up a series of films about Ben Cunnington and Nat Fyfe? The boys discuss what "CUNFE" fiction could become in the future, as well as discussing the career of North Melbourne player Shaun Atley, a pocket profile analysis on Harry Himmelberg.

item.title: 2020 - Round 7
item.description: Wil & Charlie are back talking Ben Cunnington, reviewing another Pocket Profile, reading your AFL Fan Fiction... and of course the tips for the round in footy ahead!

item.title: 2020 - Round 6
item.description: Wil & Charlie continue their journey into the world of AFL Fan Fiction, movie trailer style! There's another Pocket Profile to unpack, and, of course, the tips for the weekend in footy!

item.title: 2020 - Round 5
item.description: Wil & Charlie analyse the Pocket Profile of Sydney player George Hewitt, looking into his bucket list, inspirations and favourite band, which may or may not be called "There's a Motorcycle in the Nightclub!" Plus tips for the round ahead!

item.title: 2020 - Round 4
item.description: Wil and Charlie chat all the recent AFL developments, including the recent COVID outbreak at Essendon, as well as reviewing a Pocket Profile on Jake Lloyd!

item.title: 2020 - Round 3
item.description: Wil & Charlie discuss the week ahead in footy, read listener mail and tip for Round 3!

item.title: 2020 - Round 2
item.description: AFL is finally back and Wil & Charlie are clearly very excited about that. The guys discuss the upcoming Round 2, as well as debating who the biggest narcs in the history of the AFL are.

item.title: 2020 - Zero Footy, Lots of Mail
item.description: There still hasn't been any footy, but there's been plenty of mail sent in to the 2G1C mailbag!

item.title: 2020 - Mailbag Time
item.description: With the AFL season still on hold, it's time to dive into the 2G1C mailbag and answer some listener questions.

item.title: 2020 - There's No Footy..
item.description: The boys discuss the absence of the 2020 AFL season and the lack of football in general due to the COVID-19 pandemic, and read listener mail to keep themselves entertained.

item.title: 2020 - Week 2 Discussion
item.description: Well, it looks like the 2020 Season might be over as quickly as it began, but there's still plenty to talk about. How did the rest of the round play out? What does the future of the AFL look like? And what the heck is going on with Ben Cunnington's hair!? EMAIL THE SHOW ANY TIME: 2guys1cupAFL@gmail.com

item.title: 2020 Reacting to Match 1
item.description: Wil & Charlie talk about the eerie nature of the empty stadium in last night's season starter between Carlton & Richmond. The boys also make predictions for the remainder of Round 1.

item.title: 2020 Season Preview
item.description: Wil & Charlie are back for 2020!
